---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout title="Progression" description="RACP Basic Training learning goals and Be/Do/Know progression scales.">
  <div class="page-header">
    <h1>Learning Goals & Progression</h1>
    <p>10 learning goals. 5-point scale. This is how you get through.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>How It Works</h2>
    <p>
      The 10 learning goals articulate what trainees need to be, do, and know.
      Each is assessed on a five-point scale across the three training phases.
      Trainees must meet phase-end standards to progress or complete the program.
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Be — Competencies Scale</h2>
    <table class="level-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Level</th>
          <th>Standard</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>L1</td><td>Needs to work on behaviour in more than 5 domains of professional practice</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L2</td><td>Needs to work on behaviour in 4 or 5 domains of professional practice</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L3</td><td>Needs to work on behaviour in 2 or 3 domains of professional practice</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L4</td><td>Needs to work on behaviour in 1 domain of professional practice</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L5</td><td>Consistently behaves in line with all 10 domains of professional practice</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Do — EPA Scale</h2>
    <table class="level-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Level</th>
          <th>Standard</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>L1</td><td>Is able to be present and observe</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L2</td><td>Is able to act with direct supervision</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L3</td><td>Is able to act with indirect supervision (ready access to a supervisor)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L4</td><td>Is able to act with supervision at a distance (limited access to a supervisor)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L5</td><td>Is able to supervise others</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Know — Knowledge Guide Scale</h2>
    <table class="level-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Level</th>
          <th>Standard</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>L1</td><td>Has heard of some of the topics in this knowledge guide</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L2</td><td>Knows the topics and concepts in this knowledge guide</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L3</td><td>Knows how to apply this knowledge to practice</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L4</td><td>Frequently shows they apply this knowledge to practice</td></tr>
        <tr><td>L5</td><td>Consistently demonstrates application of this knowledge to practice</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <div class="section">
    <h2>Phase Progression</h2>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Foundation → Consolidation</div>
      <p>Meet phase-end progression criteria across Be, Do, and Know learning goals.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Consolidation → Completion</div>
      <p>Meet phase-end progression criteria. Written Examination awaits early in Completion.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <div class="card-title">Completion criteria</div>
      <p>Pass Written + Clinical Examinations. Meet all completion-level standards across all 10 learning goals.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
